                "Commentary": "India turned it on with the bat - India racked up 256, the second-highest team total in T20 World Cup history, with contributions flowing right through the top six. Abhishek Sharma broke his run of low scores with a half-century, well supported by Ishan Kishan and Suryakumar Yadav. Then came the Tilak Varma and Hardik Pandya show to provide the final flourish. Hardik also brought up a half-century as India launched 17 sixes on their way to a daunting 256. With the ball, India were not quite at their sharpest. There were moments in the field where complacency appeared to creep in, and the intensity dipped at times. Varun Chakaravarthy's lack of impact with the ball over the last two games would be a mild concern for India, and they will want their talisman back at his most threatening ahead of the next outing.",
                "Timestamp": "2026-02-26T17:40:34+00:00",
